First, I identify that the old province is "Tỉnh Vĩnh Phúc."  I know I need to check the relevant resolutions, specifically those related to province-level changes, like Resolution 60-NQ/TW.  Ah, right, this resolution indicates a merger! "Tỉnh Vĩnh Phúc" was combined with other provinces, becoming "Tỉnh Phú Thọ".  So, "Tỉnh Phú Thọ" is now the relevant province.

Next, I need to focus on "Xã Tuân Chính." Since I'm now working within the context of "Tỉnh Phú Thọ," I'll search for relevant resolutions within that province.  I found Resolution 1676/NQ-UBTVQH15, and bingo!  Line 76 is key. It explicitly states that "Xã Tuân Chính" was merged with other wards to form "Xã Thổ Tang."

Now, I'll need to double-check that "Xã Thổ Tang" exists in the list of new wards for "Tỉnh Phú Thọ."  Yep, I found it!  The JSON object confirms the existence of  "Xã Thổ Tang" with the code "09112".

The resolution explicitly mentions the merger of "Xã Tuân Chính" into "Xã Thổ Tang," and I've verified the new ward.  I'm confident I can provide an accurate answer. Therefore, I will now construct the final JSON output.
